The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for improving the reconstruction quality of compressed sensing MRI. This involves using a convolutional neural network to correct errors in the reconstruction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image and video processing. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with signal processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
